  x <- str_replace_all(string = x, pattern=" ", repl="")
  x <- as.numeric(x)
  
  return(x)
  
}

Function - get ratings

get_spi_ratings <- function(team1, team2) {
  team1_rating <- epl_spi %>% filter(name == team1) %>% select(off, def)
  team2_rating <- epl_spi %>% filter(name == team2) %>% select(off, def)
  return(list(team1_offense = team1_rating$off, team1_defense = team1_rating$def,
              team2_offense = team2_rating$off, team2_defense = team2_rating$def))
}

Function - Predict match

predict_match <- function(team1, team2, sd = 1) {
  ratings <- get_spi_ratings(team1, team2)
  team1_score <- round(rnorm(1, ratings$team1_offense, sd) * ratings$team2_defense / rnorm(1, ratings$team2_offense, sd))
  team2_score <- round(rnorm(1, ratings$team2_offense, sd) * ratings$team1_defense / rnorm(1, ratings$team1_offense, sd))
  return(list(team1_score = team1_score, team2_score = team2_score))
}

Function - Predict Winner

predict_winner <- function(team1, team2) {
  scores <- predict_match(team1, team2)
  if (scores$team1_score > scores$team2_score) {
    return(paste(team1, "is predicted to win"))
  } else if (scores$team1_score < scores$team2_score) {
    return(paste(team2, "is predicted to win"))
  } else {
    return("The match is predicted to end in a draw")
  }
}

Function - Simulate matches

simulate_matches <- function(fixture_table = pl2, times = 2){
  output_table <- data.table()
    
  # set the random seed for all simulations
  
  for (simulation_number in c(1:times)){ 
    set.seed(sample.int(1000, 1))
    for(row_number in c(1:nrow(fixture_table))){
      match_row <- fixture_table[row_number]
      
      # Get the home and away team names for the current row
      home_team <- as.character(match_row$`Home Team`)
      away_team <- as.character(match_row$`Away Team`)
      
      # Use the predict_match function to predict the scores
      scores <- predict_match(home_team, away_team)  # add random noise to the ratings
      home_score <- round(scores$team1_score)
      away_score <- round(scores$team2_score)
      
      # Use the scores to predict the winner and store it in the hda variable
      if (home_score > away_score) {
        hda <- "h"
      } else if (home_score < away_score) {
        hda <- "a"
      } else {
        hda <- "d"
      }
      
      match_row[, hda := hda]
      match_row[, simulation_id := simulation_number]
      
      output_table <- rbindlist(list(output_table, match_row), fill = T)
    }
  }
  
  return(output_table)
}

Run the simulations

nr_simlation <- 1000
simulated_matches_data <- simulate_matches(times = nr_simlation)

Simulation data

Calculate points for results

calculate_points <- function(pl2 = pl2){
  
  round_table <- data.table(team = team_names, point = 0, matched_played = 0)
  
  for (row in c(1:nrow(pl2))){
    
    result <- pl2[row]$hda
    result <- as.character(result)
    
    home_team_name <- pl2[row]$`Home Team`
    home_team_matched_played <- max(round_table[team == home_team_name]$matched_played)
    home_team_point_before <- round_table[team == home_team_name & matched_played == home_team_matched_played]$point
    
    home_team_point <- ifelse(is.na(result), home_team_point_before + 0,
                              ifelse(result == "h", home_team_point_before + 3,
                                     ifelse(result == "d", home_team_point_before + 1,
                                            home_team_point_before + 0)))
    
    away_team_name <- pl2[row]$`Away Team`
    
    away_team_matched_played <- max(round_table[team == away_team_name]$matched_played)
    away_team_point_before <- round_table[team == away_team_name & matched_played == away_team_matched_played]$point
    
    away_team_point <- ifelse(is.na(result), away_team_point_before + 0,
                              ifelse(result == "a", away_team_point_before + 3,
                                     ifelse(result == "d", away_team_point_before + 1, away_team_point_before + 0)))
    
    round_table <-rbindlist(list(round_table, data.table(matched_played = home_team_matched_played + 1,
                                                         team = home_team_name,
                                                         point = home_team_point)),
                            fill = T)
    
    round_table <-rbindlist(list(round_table, data.table(matched_played = away_team_matched_played + 1,
                                                         team = away_team_name,
                                                         point = away_team_point)),
                            fill = T)
    
  }
  
  return(round_table)
  
}

Get team names to calculate standings

team_names <- unique(c(pl2$`Home Team`, pl2$`Away Team`))

Create standings

simulate_standings <- function(all_matches = simulated_matches_data){
  
  standings_all <- data.table()
  
  for (fixtures in c(1:max(all_matches$simulation_id))){
    
    one_simulation <- all_matches[simulation_id == fixtures]
    
    simulated_fixtures <- calculate_points(one_simulation)
    simulated_fixtures[, simulation_id:= fixtures]
    
    standings_all <- rbindlist(list(standings_all, simulated_fixtures), fill = T)
    
  }
  
  return(standings_all)
  
}
simulated_standings <- simulate_standings()

Get average max point for the simulations

simulated_standings2 <-
